					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">I've seen a phenomenon when I play NES games on my CRT TV: In certain scenes, there are green stripes on the left side:<br /><br /><img src="http://i62.tinypic.com/2hq5k75.jpg" alt="Image" /><br />(&quot;Ninja Gaiden&quot;)<br /><br /><img src="http://i58.tinypic.com/a132mx.jpg" alt="Image" /><br />(&quot;Soccer League - Winner's Cup&quot;)<br /><br /><br />But this is not a general issue. Most scenes <em>don't</em> have it:<br /><br /><img src="http://i61.tinypic.com/jgjzox.jpg" alt="Image" /><br />(&quot;Ninja Gaiden&quot;)<br /><br /><img src="http://i62.tinypic.com/2j5axle.jpg" alt="Image" /><br />(&quot;Soccer League - Winner's Cup&quot;)<br /><br /><img src="http://i60.tinypic.com/9r0hdy.jpg" alt="Image" /><br />(&quot;Zelda II - The Adventure of Link&quot;)<br /><br />Also, until now, I've never seen this with scenes where black isn't the dominant color on screen.<br /><br /><br />Does anybody know what this is all about? Is it a phenomenon that's specific to my TV or have other people observed it as well? And what's the technical explanation that some scenes in NES games produce those green stripes, but most don't?<br /><br />(Also, the phenomenon is not random. If a certain scene produces the stripes, then it will always produce them. And if a scene is fine, it will always be fine. So, it doesn't happen that one and the same scene sometimes has the stripes and sometimes doesn't.)</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

