					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle">Drag wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">The NTSC signal does not require a television to disable the electron gun during h-blank and v-blank (and indeed, a lot of TVs don't because it's just extra circuitry), but that doesn't mean that there <em>aren't</em> TVs that do it anyway.</div><br />TVs that don't add their own blanking will show artifacts on authentic copies of VHS and DVD videos that use Rovi's Macrovision analog copy protection.</div>

